@page "/presets"
@using AuralizeBlazor.Options

<PageTitle>Presets</PageTitle>


<DocsPageSection>
    <SectionHeader Title="Presets">
        <Description>
            For all properties you can set Presets with class <CodeInline>AuralizerPreset</CodeInline><br />
            Some preconfigured presets are static available in the <CodeInline>AuralizerPreset</CodeInline> class and a list of all can be retrieved by <CodeInline>AuralizerPreset.All</CodeInline>.<br />
            You can also create your own presets by creating a new instance of <CodeInline>AuralizerPreset</CodeInline> and set the properties you want to change.<br/>
            In the auralizer component you can set the <CodeInline>InitialPreset</CodeInline> property to set the initial preset. Also you can set the <CodeInline>Presets</CodeInline> property to pass presets the user is able to change with mousewheel or other custom action.
        </Description>
    </SectionHeader>
    <SectionContent Outlined="true" FullWidth="true">
        <PresetsExample />
    </SectionContent>
    <SectionSource Code="@nameof(PresetsExample)" />
</DocsPageSection>

